.TH "cpumask_local_spread" 9 "cpumask_local_spread" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpumask_local_spread \- select the i'th cpu with local numa cpu's first
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" cpumask_local_spread
.BI "(unsigned int i "  ","
.BI "int node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "i" 12
index number
.IP "node" 12
local numa_node
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function selects an online CPU according to a numa aware policy;
local cpus are returned first, followed by non-local ones, then it
wraps around.

It's not very efficient, but useful for setup.
